There is no return 110111 this gild among the Chancery Gild Certilicates of 1389, but as these are probably not complete, this is no certain argument that the gild had ceased to exist. Until the oon· veyances and wills preserved in college muniment·rooms have been calendared a work too long neglected, we must be content to rest upon the presumption that the gild lapsed early in the reign 01 Richard II. The causes of its downfall may well be closely associated with the story of the rising of 1381, but at present we can only guess what actually happened.
